			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Joseph Bathanti </span></strong>teaches creative writing at Appalachian State University in Boone, North Carolina. He is the author of four books of poetry, the most recent of which, <em>This Metal </em>(Saint Andrews Press), won the Oscar Arnold Young Award. His first novel, <em>East Liberty</em> (Banks Channel Books), won the 2001 Carolina Novel Award. He lives in Statesville, North Carolina, with his wife and two sons.</p><a href="/contributors/joseph-bathanti" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
